How to Get started with Fashion Freelancing
1. Choose your niche
2. Find 10 to 15 prospective small fashion brands online.
3. Research on what the pain points are
4. Choose what services you will provide.
5. Stay visible on social media
6. Get your portfolio together .
7. Connect with prospectives online

Ready to level-up your Fashion Career?

I am  conducting a 5 Day  Workshop on "How to Create Fashion Flat Sketches in less than 6 minutes, that are professional & techpack friendly.

Calling out all
- Fashion Students
- Existing Fashion Designers
- Freelance Fashion Designers
- Technical Designers in Fashion
- Anyone interested to work in the Fashion Industry
Here is what you are going to discover during our 3 days together and unlock Rs.45000/- worth of bonuses,

 Day 1 - The 3 most important tools in Adobe Illustrator
          What are tech packs & where is Adobe Illustrator used in Fashion Industry

 Day 2 - The Step by Step blueprint to create any flat sketch in less than 6 Minutes
         Tricks to create a beautiful professional looking sketch, suitable for tech packs.

 Day 3 - How to Colour & Recolour even complex artwork, with a single Click

 Day 4 - How to Create Trims & Detailing like Gathers & ruffles in such a way that they can be reused over & over again for a lifetime, without drawing from scratch

 Day 5 - How to make your sketch techpack Friendly

Bonus Lessons:

 How to use Illustrator in the Fashion Industry, even if you have no prior education in Fashion

 How to find Pantone shades without a Pantone book

 How to create colour palettes for your design projects

.How to Create a Portfolio that makes you look like an expert

 How to find your dream Fashion job or Freelance client

 How to use social media as a Fashion Designer to achieve your desired success
